honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl

Class BluetoothConfiguration_ExPCL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.PrinterData_ExPCL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.PrinterState_ExPCL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.BluetoothConfiguration_ExPCL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BluetoothConfiguration_ExPCL
extends PrinterState_ExPCL
    This class handles the data from an Bluetooth AT Command query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    *AGLNLocal Name.
    *AGLCLocal COD.
    *AMPMPower Save Mode.
    *AGSMSecurity Mode.
    *AGDMDiscoverability Mode.
    *AGCMConnectability Mode.
    *AGPMPairing Mode.
    *AILBALocal Bluetooth Address.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • BluetoothConfiguration_ExPCL

        public BluetoothConfiguration_ExPCL(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_ExPCL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        Indicates if getSecurity() parameter is present.
